<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[178,1085,768,851]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">
Etymology: The specific epithet (adjective) alludes to the weakly pronounced lateral carinae on the ventral process of the aedeagus, the most evident character distinguishing this species from the similar 
<taxonomicName authority="ASSING, 2011" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[620,913,829,850]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicata">
<emphasis box="[620,763,829,850]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. complicata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[770,913,829,850]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" pagination="137 - 183" refId="ref7350" refString="ASSING V. (2011): On the Staphylinidae (Coleoptera) of Iran. II. New species and additional records, with special reference to the Paederinae, Xantholinini, and Aleocharinae. - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde Serie A, Neue Serie 4: 137 - 183." type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[178,1085,868,951]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">
Description: Body length 
<quantity box="[539,659,868,890]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.15" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" unit="mm" value="4.15" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="3.6">3.6-4.7 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 1.7-2.0 mm. External characters (
<figureCitation box="[297,412,898,920]" captionStart="Figs 44-51" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1506,1528]" captionTargetBox="[183,1075,212,1478]" captionTargetId="figure-75@16.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 44-51: Oxypoda subplicata nov.sp.: (44) habitus; (45) forebody; (46) antenna; (47-49) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (50) paramere; (51) spermatheca. Scale bars: 44: 1.0 mm; 45-46: 0.5 mm; 47-50: 0.2 mm; 51: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5183278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5183278/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Figs 44-46</figureCitation>
) as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[487,633,898,920]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicata">
<emphasis box="[487,633,898,920]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. complicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other species allied to 
<taxonomicName authority="(MANNERHEIM, 1830)" baseAuthorityName="MANNERHEIM" baseAuthorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis box="[926,1085,898,920]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. abdominalis</emphasis>
(MANNERHEIM, 1830)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[178,1085,966,1112]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">
♂: sternite VIII acutely produced posteriorly; median lobe of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[961,1078,968,990]" captionStart="Figs 44-51" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1506,1528]" captionTargetBox="[183,1075,212,1478]" captionTargetId="figure-75@16.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 44-51: Oxypoda subplicata nov.sp.: (44) habitus; (45) forebody; (46) antenna; (47-49) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (50) paramere; (51) spermatheca. Scale bars: 44: 1.0 mm; 45-46: 0.5 mm; 47-50: 0.2 mm; 51: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5183278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5183278/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Figs 47-49</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[178,321,998,1020]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" metricValueMax="5.4" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" unit="mm" value="0.53" valueMax="0.54" valueMin="0.52">0.52-0.54 mm</quantity>
long; ventral process laterally with indistinct carinae (best visible in lateral view), with rather large, but acute apex (lateral view); crista apicalis small; paramere (
<figureCitation box="[186,261,1060,1082]" captionStart="Figs 44-51" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1506,1528]" captionTargetBox="[183,1075,212,1478]" captionTargetId="figure-75@16.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 44-51: Oxypoda subplicata nov.sp.: (44) habitus; (45) forebody; (46) antenna; (47-49) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (50) paramere; (51) spermatheca. Scale bars: 44: 1.0 mm; 45-46: 0.5 mm; 47-50: 0.2 mm; 51: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5183278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5183278/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
) approximately 
<quantity box="[430,521,1060,1082]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" unit="mm" value="0.75">0.75 mm</quantity>
long, apical lobe long and slender, approximately half as long as basal portion of paramere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[178,1085,1129,1182]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">
<specimenCount box="[178,191,1132,1155]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: posterior margin of sternite VIII weakly concave in the middle; spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[1003,1077,1129,1151]" captionStart="Figs 44-51" captionStartId="16.[178,218,1506,1528]" captionTargetBox="[183,1075,212,1478]" captionTargetId="figure-75@16.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs 44-51: Oxypoda subplicata nov.sp.: (44) habitus; (45) forebody; (46) antenna; (47-49) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (50) paramere; (51) spermatheca. Scale bars: 44: 1.0 mm; 45-46: 0.5 mm; 47-50: 0.2 mm; 51: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5183278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5183278/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
) not distinctive.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="1136" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[178,1085,1197,1601]" lastBlockId="17.[178,1085,219,300]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="1136" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">
Comparative notes: As can be inferred from the similar external appearance (body shape, punctation, long legs, apically weakly incrassate antennae) and the similar sexual characters (shape and internal structures of the median lobe of the aedeagus; shape of the spermatheca), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2016" box="[570,708,1285,1307]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subplicata">
<emphasis box="[570,708,1285,1307]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. subplicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="MANNERHEIM" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[927,1085,1285,1307]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis box="[927,1085,1285,1307]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its allies, which are reliably distinguished only based on the shape of the median lobe of the aedeagus. Aside from the widespread 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="MANNERHEIM" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[715,875,1344,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis box="[715,875,1344,1365]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the geographically close representatives of this group in the Middle East and Middle Asia are 
<taxonomicName authority="ASSING, 2006" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ziyaretica">
<emphasis box="[953,1085,1374,1395]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. ziyaretica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[178,319,1403,1425]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" pagination="277 - 331" refId="ref7272" refString="ASSING V. (2006): On some species of Oxypoda MANNERHEIM from Turkey and adjacent regions (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 38 (1): 277 - 331." type="journal article" year="2006">ASSING, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(central southern 
<collectingCountry box="[504,595,1403,1425]" name="Turkey" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="ASSING, 2009" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2009" box="[613,887,1403,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustior">
<emphasis box="[613,739,1403,1424]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. robustior</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[746,887,1403,1424]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" pagination="1307 - 1315" refId="ref7313" refString="ASSING V. (2009): On some Oxypoda species of the subgenus Sphenoma MANNERHEIM (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 41 (2): 1307 - 1315." type="journal article" year="2009">ASSING, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[901,946,1403,1425]" name="Iran" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Iran</collectingCountry>
), 
<emphasis box="[964,1085,1403,1424]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. kirgisica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[178,320,1432,1453]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" pagination="1307 - 1315" refId="ref7313" refString="ASSING V. (2009): On some Oxypoda species of the subgenus Sphenoma MANNERHEIM (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 41 (2): 1307 - 1315." type="journal article" year="2009">ASSING, 2009</bibRefCitation>
(
<collectingCountry box="[336,458,1432,1454]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="ASSING, 2012" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2012" box="[478,736,1432,1453]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ludgeri">
<emphasis box="[478,584,1432,1453]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. ludgeri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[593,736,1432,1453]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" pagination="365 - 399" refId="ref7402" refString="ASSING V. (2012): On the taxonomy and zoogeography of some Oxypoda species of the West Palaearctic region (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 44 (1): 365 - 399." type="journal article" year="2012">ASSING, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[751,873,1432,1454]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
), and 
<taxonomicName authority="ASSING, 2011" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicata">
<emphasis box="[939,1085,1432,1453]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. complicata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[178,320,1462,1483]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" pagination="137 - 183" refId="ref7350" refString="ASSING V. (2011): On the Staphylinidae (Coleoptera) of Iran. II. New species and additional records, with special reference to the Paederinae, Xantholinini, and Aleocharinae. - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde Serie A, Neue Serie 4: 137 - 183." type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[335,381,1462,1483]" name="Iran" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Iran</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[393,611,1461,1483]" country="Iran" name="Azarbayjan-e Gharbi" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Azarbayjan-e Gharbi</collectingRegion>
; East 
<collectingCountry box="[675,752,1461,1483]" name="Turkey" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Turkey</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[764,857,1462,1483]" country="Turkey" name="Erzurum" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">Erzurum</collectingRegion>
). The aedeagus of the new species is most similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[626,777,1491,1512]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicata">
<emphasis box="[626,777,1491,1512]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. complicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by the weakly pronounced carinae on the ventral process of the aedeagus. In other respects, both species are extremely similar. Based on the currently available material, this difference is constant. From the sympatric 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="MANNERHEIM" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[480,636,1579,1600]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis box="[480,636,1579,1600]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2016" box="[649,785,1579,1600]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subplicata">
<emphasis box="[649,785,1579,1600]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1134">O. subplicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished particularly by the much stouter apex of the ventral process of the aedeagus. For illustrations of the aedeagi of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[298,446,248,269]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicata">
<emphasis box="[298,446,248,269]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1136">O. complicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="MANNERHEIM" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[724,885,248,269]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="1136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis box="[724,885,248,269]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1136">O. abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group see 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" pageId="17" pageNumber="1136" pagination="277 - 331" refId="ref7272" refString="ASSING V. (2006): On some species of Oxypoda MANNERHEIM from Turkey and adjacent regions (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 38 (1): 277 - 331." type="journal article" year="2006">ASSING (2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[250,303,278,299]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1136" pagination="1307 - 1315" refId="ref7313" refString="ASSING V. (2009): On some Oxypoda species of the subgenus Sphenoma MANNERHEIM (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 41 (2): 1307 - 1315." type="journal article" year="2009">2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[313,366,278,299]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1136" pagination="137 - 183" refId="ref7350" refString="ASSING V. (2011): On the Staphylinidae (Coleoptera) of Iran. II. New species and additional records, with special reference to the Paederinae, Xantholinini, and Aleocharinae. - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde Serie A, Neue Serie 4: 137 - 183." type="journal article" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[377,432,278,300]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1136" pagination="365 - 399" refId="ref7402" refString="ASSING V. (2012): On the taxonomy and zoogeography of some Oxypoda species of the West Palaearctic region (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 44 (1): 365 - 399." type="journal article" year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
