<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="1136" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[178,1085,315,425]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1136">
Distribution and natural history: The 
<typeStatus box="[855,891,315,336]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1136">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected in three localities to the south and southwest of Kapan, South 
<collectingCountry box="[954,1045,344,366]" name="Armenia" pageId="17" pageNumber="1136">Armenia</collectingCountry>
, by sifting moist leaf litter and debris in oak forests and along a stream at altitudes of 
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.12" metricValueMax="2.19" metricValueMin="2.05" pageId="17" pageNumber="1136" unit="m" value="2120.0" valueMax="2190.0" valueMin="2050.0">2050- 2190 m</quantity>
. Part of the material is teneral.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
